arch:property.oc:show_val: This locus represents the 31 floor pavers lifted to conduct the sounding. Eight east west rows of pavers were removed. All pavers received both a number from 1-31 and a sequence number. Some of the pavers broke during removal. All pavers were stacked east west across the W CP East to form a low barrier wall at the north side of the sounding. The smaller fragments were numbered to correspond and stored in a crate in the LW-7 storage trench.

Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre-CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. At this time the northwest subterranean channel is damaged and clogged with CE 1st c. pottery. Repairs are made to the Hexagonal Pavement as well as to the East Exedra walls. Bath Complex built.
4.0 m north south-by-4.30 m east west.
